knop
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:a small hollow sphere of wool used as a fill product and for soaking up oil spills.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See: woolspill
Pronunciation:
Notes:
Citations
Date:  0/0/1991
Source:  A to Z Glossary of Wool Terms
Author:  SQUiRE
Vol / Page:  24
Edition:
Quote:  Knops - are small spheres of wool. The most used are soft knops which are hollow and are an ideal fill for pillows, duvets and chair swabs. They are also useful for soaking up oil spills. They have high bulk and resilience, and are fire resistant.
