Date:  0/0/1991
Source:  A to Z Glossary of Wool Terms
Author:  SQUiRE
Vol / Page:  44
Edition:
Quote:  Woolspill - a WRONZ [Wool Research Organisation of NZ] developed product by which floating booms filled with wool soft knops, trapping up to forty times their own weight, can mop up oil spills.
